snippet: Prime Minister Nuri Kamal al-Maliki of Iraq visited the Kurdistan region for the first time in more than two years in an effort to resolve an oil and land dispute.
abstract: Prime Min Nuri Kamal al-Maliki of Iraq visits Kurdistan region for first time in more than two years, symbolic step toward resolving long-running dispute over oil and land; better relations with Kurds could relieve pressure on Maliki and his Shiite-led government in coping with surge in sectarian violence spilling over from Syria.
lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Nuri Kamal al-Maliki of Iraq visited the Kurdistan region for the first time in more than two years in an effort to resolve an oil and land dispute.

headline.main: Rare Visit to Kurds by Iraqi Leader
headline.print_headline: Rare Visit to Kurds By Iraqi Leader
